cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM 

The paper focuses on utilizing deep visual semantic features and text-based item attributes to discover trending styles in Overstock. This involves techniques such as Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA) and Polylingual Latent Dirichlet Allocation (PolyLDA), which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves indexing activations within convolutional layers, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
